{
  "message": "test(corpus): add 2026-02-12 macOS dogfood pattern samples\n\nAdd live-captured pattern corpus samples from dogfood testing on macOS\n(2026-02-12), providing ground-truth test fixtures for the pattern\ndetection engine.\n\nEach sample includes three files:\n- .txt: raw terminal output captured from a live agent session\n- .expect.json: expected pattern match results (rule IDs, captures, etc.)\n- .meta.json: capture metadata (agent type, OS, terminal, timestamp)\n\nSamples added:\n- claude_code/compaction_dogfood: Claude Code context compaction event\n  triggered during a live coding session\n- codex/device_code_dogfood: Codex device code authentication flow\n  captured during OAuth device authorization\n- codex/usage_reached_dogfood: Codex usage limit reached notification\n  from a session hitting the API quota ceiling\n- gemini/session_summary_dogfood: Gemini CLI session summary output\n  showing token usage and cost breakdown\n\nThese complement the existing synthetic corpus samples with real-world\ncaptures that exercise edge cases in agent output formatting, ANSI\nescape sequences, and terminal state that synthetic samples may miss.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
